get.summary: Search for an area by name and area type ID. Can be useful for finding the area code (e.g. for use in other API calls) if you only have a name for an area.

parameters.name: search_text
parameters.description: Text to search for

parameters.name: area_type_ids
parameters.description: IDs of the area types to search for. Multiple IDs can be provided, separated by commas (e.g. '54,56,58,60,63' for CCG or sub-ICB locations)

get.summary: Retrieve the parent area that contains a given area. (e.g. what PCN a GP practice is in, or what ICB a CCG is in)

parameters.name: child_area_code
parameters.description: Area code of the area whose parent area is to be retrieved

parameters.name: parent_area_type_ids
parameters.description: Area type ID(s) of the parent area types to retrieve. Multiple IDs can be provided, separated by commas (e.g. '54,56,58,60,63' for CCG or sub-ICB locations)

get.summary: Retrieve information on an area code or common separated list of area codes. Useful when you have retrieved an area code from another API call and want basic details on it (e.g. its name).

parameters.name: area_codes
parameters.description: List of area codes. Multiple area codes can be provided, separated by commas (e.g. 'K84056,K84057' for two GP practices)

get.summary: Retrieve child areas contained within a parent area (e.g. all GP practices in a PCN or LSOAs in a council area).

parameters.name: area_type_id
parameters.description: Area type ID of the child area type to retrieve. Only a single area type ID can be provided at a time.

parameters.name: parent_area_code
parameters.description: Area code of the parent area whose child areas are to be retrieved

parameters.name: profile_id
parameters.description: Profile ID [optional]

get.summary: Gets the address for a given area code (including latitude and longitude). Useful when you have retrieved an area code from another API call and want the address.

parameters.name: area_code
parameters.description: Area code of the area whose address is to be retrieved

get.summary: Get breakdown of size of GP registered population by 5-year 'quinary' age bands (for a PCN or individual GP practice). For individual GP practices, also get the total registered population at that practice.

parameters.name: area_code
parameters.description: Area code for the GP practice or PCN to get the population breakdown for

parameters.name: area_type_id
parameters.description: Area type ID. Either '7' for GP practice or '204' for Primary Care Network (PCN)

parameters.name: data_point_offset
parameters.description: [Optional] Number of years prior to the latest available year to get the data for (i.e. if '0' returns period of 2024, '1' would return 2023, '2' would return 2022, etc.) [Default is 0]

get.summary: Get summary information for a GP practice given its area code. Only works for GP practices (with area type ID of 7). The summary information includes non-white ethnicity breakdown, deprivation, CQC rating, % satisfaction score, male and female life expectancy and QOF achievement.

parameters.name: area_code
parameters.description: Area code for the GP practice

parameters.name: area_type_id
parameters.description: Area type ID for GP practice (i.e. only accepts '7')

parameters.name: data_point_offset
parameters.description: Time period offset from the data point (i.e. latest available time period) [Default is 0]

get.summary: Gets a list of available indicators for a given profile ID and area type ID. Useful for finding what indicators are available for a certain area type and profile before retrieving the data using `Data_GetDataForSpecificArea`
get.description: The indicators are differentiated by age and sex where appropriate. Returns a list of group root summaries.

parameters.name: profile_id
parameters.description: Profile ID

parameters.name: area_type_id
parameters.description: Area type ID

get.summary: Retrieve the latest value for a given indicator ID and area code.

parameters.name: area_type_id
parameters.description: Area type ID of the area you are retrieving the indicator for

parameters.name: area_code
parameters.description: Area code of the area you are retrieving the indicator for

parameters.name: indicator_ids
parameters.description: Indicator IDs you wish to get values for. If you want to find multiple indicator ID values at once provide a comma-separated list.

parameters.name: restrict_to_profile_ids
parameters.description: IGNORE THIS PARAMETER.

Ethnicity.description: Estimated proportions for non-white ethnic groups in the practice population. White ethnicity is not included in this breakdown.

GpDeprivationDecile.description: Deprivation decile (1-10) of the GP practice area. Higher values indicate LOWER deprivation - a score of 10 is lowest possible deprivation and 1 is highest level of deprivation.

CQCRatingID.description: CQC rating (1-4). 4 is outstanding, 3 is good, 2 is requires improvement, 1 is inadequate.

CQCRatingReportLink.description: URL to the CQC rating report

Denom.description: Total number of possible QOF points

Val.description: % of possible QOF points that have been achieved
% having a positive experience of their practice based on GP patient survey data

IndicatorName.description: Description of what data point the indicator represents

Sex.description: The groups of sex the indicator covers

Age.description: The age or age range the indicator covers

DateChanges.description: When the indicator was last updated

DataQualityNote.description: Any data quality notes associated with the indicator

TimePeriod.description: The time period the indicator covers

Unit.description: The unit of measurement that the indicator is measured in (e.g. per 100,000, %, etc.)

ValueType.description: The method that the indicator value was calculated by (e.g. directly standardised rate, crude rate, etc.)

YearRange.description: How many whole years are covered by the time period the indicator is measured over

Data.description: List of values (with confidence intervals and raw counts) for the indicator

Sex.description: The groups of sex the indicator covers

Age.description: The age or age range the indicator covers

IndicatorId.description: Indicator ID for the indicator which explains the meaning of this value

AreaCode.description: Area code this value relates to

Year.description: Year that the value relates to

YearRange.description: How many years the value covers

LoCI.description: Lower confidence interval for the value of the indicator

UpCI.description: Upper confidence interval for the value of the indicator

Count.description: Raw count value for the indicator (i.e. the true value of the indicator before it has been standardised for population, etc.)

Values.description: Percentage (%) of total population in that age and sex band given as two arrays (1=male, 2=female). Each array follows same order as 'Labels' array.

PopulationTotals.description: Population totals by age and sex given as two arrays (1=male, 2=female). Each array follows same order as 'Labels' array.

Period.description: Year to which the population data relates

ChildAreaCount.description: For PCNs only - the number of practices in that PCN

ListSize.description: For GP practices only - the total registered population at that practice

Val.description: Total registered population at that practice
